    title="🖋"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f58b.svg">️
But somewhere between shrinking walls and rising prices,
control quietly slipped away.

A van teaches a different rhythm.
Peace that’s maintained by your own hands.
Space that expands because it’s yours. <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🌿"
    title="herb"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f33f.svg">

No coping strategies.
No chemical calm.
No permission required.

Just the quiet power of choosing where you rest,
when you move,
and what you protect. <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🔑"
    title="key"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f511.svg">

This isn’t escape — it’s reclamation.
Not running from the world,
but stepping back into agency.

Own your space.
Own your rhythm.
Own your peace. <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🌄"
