<div class=chatlog__message-group><div id=chatlog__message-container-1469615561561346088 class=chatlog__message-container data-message-id=1469615561561346088><div class=chatlog__message><div class=chatlog__message-aside><img class=chatlog__avatar src=https://cdn.discordapp.com/embed/avatars/4.png alt=Avatar loading=lazy></div><div class=chatlog__message-primary><div class=chatlog__header><span class=chatlog__author title=dadventuressteve data-user-id=1264035953933156432>Veilocity</span> <span class=chatlog__timestamp title="Saturday, 7 February 2026 12:47 PM"><a href=#chatlog__message-container-1469615561561346088>7/02/2026 12:47 PM</a></span></div><div class="chatlog__content chatlog__markdown"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve><strong>Prune With Awareness - Not Forgetfulness ✂️<img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="💚"
    title="green_heart"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f49a.svg"> 13/11/2025 - T&#252;rkiye</strong>

We are all pruning every day.
Every thought released.
Every belief shed.
Every habit outgrown.
This is how the inner garden is shaped.

Pruning is not ego death.
It is discernment —
removing what was added through fear, conditioning, and inheritance,
so what is true can breathe again.

Jesus said the Kingdom belongs to the children —
reinforcing the intent to shed the conditioning
that was never yours to begin with.

At the Last Supper, Jesus said:
“This is my body, given for you.”
This was not an instruction for blind repetition,
but a call to remembrance —
to keep the meaning of this way of being from disappearing.

Remembrance without presence is not remembrance at all.
Ritual repeated without awareness does not honor the sacrifice —
it forgets it.

When we prune consciously,
we protect the most important part of ourselves…
<img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🌸"
    title="cherry_blossom"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f338.svg"> the inner child —
not na&#239;ve,
but awake.

Tend your garden with awareness.
To repeat the cycle without understanding
is simply to stunt your growth.

