It shows choice and participation,
while quietly reflecting the currency that funds it.

Choice without change.
Speech without reach.
Protest contained within the system.

In theory, democracy is free.
In practice, it is purchased.
And what purchases it defines its limits.

So democracy becomes a mirror of the Dollar —
not by intent,
but by consequence.

War once forced change,
but war is no longer the way.
It destroys what we are meant to preserve.

Peace cannot be conquered.
It cannot be enforced.
Peace must be belonged to.

In unity of being.
At peace.

