This debate exists because people care — they’re just responding to the same pain in different ways.
Some react from grief and urgency; others from exhaustion and compassion fatigue. Both are human.

The problem isn’t empathy — it’s a system that circulates suffering without resolving its causes.
Charity should preserve dignity and lead to liberation, not prolonged dependence or division.

The goal is simple: stability, dignity, and a world where helping no longer requires broadcasting pain.

