(Extended Version — Includes 20 Minutes of Additional Footage)

This isn’t just a personal story — it’s about narcissism operating at scale.

Narcissism thrives on control, confusion, dependency, and exhaustion. When systems lose accountability, they begin to mirror the same traits: gaslighting, blame-shifting, silencing, and punishment for autonomy.

During my separation, I witnessed how legal processes, financial pressure, and mental-health narratives can be misused to strip self-agency and keep people trapped inside an expanding loop — one that drains energy, identity, and hope.

I’m sharing this not from anger, but clarity. When narcissism becomes structural, it no longer looks like a person — it looks like policy, procedure, and “just how things work.”

If you’ve been made to doubt your reality, punished for speaking truth, or forced to survive instead of heal — you’re not broken. You’re reacting to a system built without empathy.

Awareness collapses the loop.

