In this reflection, I explore the difference between true spiritual release and the modern version of forgiveness that often becomes reconciliation, bargaining, or emotional agreement.

From my own experience, I’ve found that saying “I forgive you” doesn’t always remove the wound — sometimes the only real path forward is simply to let go, heal, and trust God with what we cannot carry.

Peace doesn’t come from another person’s apology or permission.

Ultimately, forgiveness belongs to God.

If someone seeks forgiveness, perhaps the true source is not another human — but the Divine.

Let go of what no longer serves.
Let God handle what you cannot.

Food for thought.

