<div class=chatlog__message-group><div id=chatlog__message-container-1470122873694715924 class=chatlog__message-container data-message-id=1470122873694715924><div class=chatlog__message><div class=chatlog__message-aside><img class=chatlog__avatar src=https://cdn.discordapp.com/embed/avatars/4.png alt=Avatar loading=lazy></div><div class=chatlog__message-primary><div class=chatlog__header><span class=chatlog__author title=dadventuressteve data-user-id=1264035953933156432>Veilocity</span> <span class=chatlog__timestamp title="Sunday, 8 February 2026 10:23 PM"><a href=#chatlog__message-container-1470122873694715924>8/02/2026 10:23 PM</a></span></div><div class="chatlog__content chatlog__markdown"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve><strong>Redirection <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🌬"
    title="🌬"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f32c.svg">️ 27/12/2025 - VOID</strong>

I wanted to check in and be transparent.

Update: In the video I mention that I had created a new Instagram account. Unfortunately, since recording it, that account has also been shut down. I’ve now created three separate Instagram accounts, each tied to a unique email address — and every single one has been suspended or disabled.

Each time, I’m told I’ve violated the platform’s terms and conditions.
Yet my most recent account had only one video uploaded before it was shut down.

I won’t pretend it hasn’t left me feeling a bit defeated — not because of ego or numbers, but because the content I share is shaped by what I’m shown on its platform — and sometimes what I see feels like a maze. My intention has always been to help point toward the exits.

So when something like this keeps happening, it leaves very little room for guessing intent.

#CheckIn #Redirection #Clarity #CreatorJourney #StillMoving #AdaptAndGrow #Gratitude #Perspective #Resilience

