<div class=chatlog__message-group><div id=chatlog__message-container-1470157047189340252 class=chatlog__message-container data-message-id=1470157047189340252><div class=chatlog__message><div class=chatlog__message-aside><img class=chatlog__avatar src=https://cdn.discordapp.com/embed/avatars/4.png alt=Avatar loading=lazy></div><div class=chatlog__message-primary><div class=chatlog__header><span class=chatlog__author title=dadventuressteve data-user-id=1264035953933156432>Veilocity</span> <span class=chatlog__timestamp title="Monday, 9 February 2026 12:39 AM"><a href=#chatlog__message-container-1470157047189340252>9/02/2026 12:39 AM</a></span></div><div class="chatlog__content chatlog__markdown"><span class=chatlog__markdown-preserve><strong>Fatherhood woven in... Still Carrying Them With Me <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="👨"
    title="man"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f468.svg">‍<img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="👦"
    title="boy"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f466.svg"><img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🫀"
    title="anatomical_heart"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1fac0.svg"><img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🌅"
    title="sunrise"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f305.svg"> 20/12/2025 - VOID</strong>

I stepped away from the city for a few days and went off-grid.
After 7 straight days of rain and ~10&#176;C, working in the cold was tough.
Being back at an electrical campsite for a bit has actually been really nice — warm, stable, refilled the water tanks, reset the body.

I’ve been thinking about heading back to the city soon.
I do miss inline skating, and the weather’s finally turned good again.

I also miss my boys — Christian and Joshua. Always. <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🤍"
    title="white_heart"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f90d.svg">

Something else came up while reflecting:
The truth is, I was in survival mode for much of my marriage.
I was a go-getter for the family — always running errands, fixing problems, carrying momentum.
And there were times I’d get home, sit in the car, and just… pause.
Not because I didn’t want to go inside — but because it all felt heavy.

What I don’t miss is the chaos of this holiday season.
It’s kind of absurd when you think about it — an extended holiday where you’re expected to serve everyone but yourself.

Right now, I’m choosing a little quiet, a little warmth, and a little honesty.

Love 
