It speaks in freedom and opportunity,
yet moves by extraction.

It collapses human possibility into price,
then quietly devalues it through manipulation.

Hands are kept busy,
but the work never completes.
Energy is spent,
rest is deferred.

What is measured grows.
What is living thins.

This is not abundance.
It is hunger dressed as progress.

Peace does not arise
where everything has a price.

