Every connection begins in awe of what makes us different.
But then comes the urge to control, to alter, and when resistance rises — to delete.

Yet the soul was never meant to be debugged by another.
It’s already imperfectly perfect.

The moment we try to rewrite someone’s essence, we fight the oldest command in existence:
“Know thyself.”

<img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
