Friday check-in. Had to leave my good internet spot after the kitchen faucet micro switch broke — no dishes in the bathroom if I can help it <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="😅"
    title="sweat_smile"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f605.svg"> Improvised a bypass switch from a lamp and got the water flowing again.

It’s 10&#176;C, raining, internet’s slow, emotions up and down. Some days staying present is the only way to stay steady. The past can feel like a raging fire — especially when your heart is still back there.

Also unpacking my complicated relationship with money… when you’ve seen it used as control, it changes how you see it.

Still here. Still moving. Flame on, flame off. <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🔥"
