And remember, when it gets too much, you can embody peace by letting go of the role of the needle — relinquishing control and pretending to be a flower. <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🌸"
    title="cherry_blossom"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f338.svg"> In that moment, the music no longer defines you, and peace effortlessly blooms within.

Matthew 6:28–30 reminds us: the flowers of the field do not labor or spin, yet they are clothed in beauty.

And if we get a little scientific about it — it’s the “why” that matters, from wave into form. <img
    loading="lazy"
    class="chatlog__emoji "
    alt="🌊"
    title="ocean"
    src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/twitter/twemoji@latest/assets/svg/1f30a.svg">

