Society has conditioned us to believe love is about attraction, sustaining, and maintaining. But that definition is a distortion. The truth is, love cannot be trapped in words. Love is fulfillment from within. From that overflow, true belonging flows naturally. Love does not conquer, it welcomes. It does not control, it unites. The source of love has always been within.

