This TikTok reflection centers on lawlessness—not just in action, but in silence.

When those entrusted with authority abandon truth, ignore evidence, or choose convenience over justice, lawlessness takes root within the very systems meant to uphold order. It is not always chaos in the streets—it is often quiet, documented, and filed away while harm continues.

This message explores the weight of being unseen in plain sight, and the deeper reality that lawlessness is revealed not only by what is done—but by what is allowed.

