If someone knowingly commits harm with intent — and then tries to push the karmic consequences onto someone else — that isn’t karma. That’s abuse.

I spoke up. I warned people. I provided evidence. When it became unsafe, I removed myself. Being muted or gaslit does not equal consent.

And I want this clearly stated: I do not consent to any hypothetical reincarnation loop designed to process someone else’s karma for intentional wrongdoing. No one should be forced to carry consequences for sins they did not commit.

